question: 結局
sourceMnemonic:
If you <kanji>tie</kanji> the <kanji>bureau</kanji> up with your delays this may not get done this year <vocabulary>after all</vocabulary>.

This word carries the nuance that despite the various events or factors leading up to it, the final outcome just is what it is.
sourceReadingMnemonic: This is a jukugo word, which usually means on'yomi readings from the kanji. If you know the readings of your kanji you'll know how to read this as well. Note the <ja>けつ</ja> gets changed to <ja>けっ</ja> as <ja>つ</ja>s in this situation often do.
